Ruby M. JUNE, Administratrix of the Estate of Eldon June, Deceased, Appellant, v. DETROIT EDISON COMPANY, Appel-lee. No. 8671. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 17, 1941. Bresnahan & Groefsema and John R. Rood, all of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Oxtoby, Robison & Hull, of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before ALLEN, MARTIN, and McAL-LISTER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This case came on to be heard upon the briefs and record and the argument of counsel ; and the court being of opinion that the trial court did not err in finding that no evidence of negligence on the part of the appellee was presented in the record, it is ordered that the judgment appealed from be, and it hereby is, affirmed.
